data.name: Crispy French Fries
data.quickTastyDescription: Golden and crispy French fries, a perfect side dish or snack!
detailedCookingInstructions: Peel and cut the Russet potatoes into thin strips.
Soak the potato strips in cold water for at least 30 minutes to remove excess starch.
Drain and pat the potatoes dry with a towel.
In a large pot, heat the vegetable oil over medium heat until it reaches 350°F (175°C).
Fry the potato strips in batches, cooking for about 5-7 minutes until golden brown and crispy.
Remove fries with a slotted spoon and place on paper towels to drain excess oil.
Season with salt, pepper, paprika, and garlic powder while hot.
